# Uyghur → IPA transliteration rules (ug_ipa.rules)
#
# Source: McCollum, A. G. (2021). "Transparency, locality, and contrast in Uyghur backness harmony".
#         Laboratory Phonology: Journal of the Association for Laboratory Phonology, 12(1): article 8.
#         DOI: https://doi.org/10.5334/labphon.239
#
# Simplified:
#   - 7-vowel system /ɑ æ e i y ø o u/ (+ marginal /e/)
#   - no explicit [i]~[ɯ] alternation
#   - no diphthongs, no length, no optional allophones in the core map

$V = [ɑ æ e i y ø o u];        # vowel macro (phonemic set used here)

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# One-to-one grapheme → phone map (Uyghur Arabic script)

# Consonants
ب > b ;
پ > p ;
ت > t ;
ج > d͡ʒ ;
چ > t͡ʃ ;
خ > χ ;
د > d ;
ر > r ;
ز > z ;
ژ > ʒ ;
س > s ;
ش > ʃ ;
غ > ʁ ;
ف > f ;
ق > q ;
ك > k ;
گ > ɡ ;
ڭ > ŋ ;
ل > l ;
م > m ;
ن > n ;
ھ > h ;
ۋ > w ;
ي > j ;

# Vowels
و > o ;
ۇ > u ;
ۆ > ø ;
ۈ > y ;
ا > ɑ ;
ە > æ ;
ې > e ;
ى > i ;

# Hamza (purely orthographic in standard Uyghur)
ئ >  ;       # deletion

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ADDITIONS 2025-12-02: Missing chars found in OSCAR corpus audit
# See docs/ipa-rules-refactor.md
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Missing Arabic consonants
ع > ʕ ;       # AIN - pharyngeal fricative
ح > ħ ;       # HAH - voiceless pharyngeal fricative
ء > ʔ ;       # HAMZA standalone - glottal stop

# Arabic punctuation (normalize to space)
، >  ;        # ARABIC COMMA
؟ >  ;        # ARABIC QUESTION MARK
ـ >  ;        # TATWEEL (kashida stretcher)

# Arabic diacritics (delete - optional short vowel marks)
َ >  ;        # FATHA
ِ >  ;        # KASRA
ُ >  ;        # DAMMA
ْ >  ;        # SUKUN
ّ >  ;        # SHADDA

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

